3.plot: Craig McCracken has given the world some of the coolest cartoons in the last 20 years, including "The Powerpuff Girls", "Foster's Home For Imaginary Friends" and most recently "Wander Over Yonder". He's even been known to throw in some subtle throwbacks to his previous works in his newer shows, but could some CHARACTERS have actually carried over as well? This week on Cartoon Conspiracy, Emily will attempt to determine whether Creaky Pete from "Foster's Home For Imaginary Friends" is actually Wander from "Wander Over Yonder".

4.title: The Beauty and the Beast Theory - Gaston Prince Charming?
4.plot: "Beauty and the Beast" is one of the most treasured Disney animated films of all time, and it's only made better by it's incredible cast characters. They transcended the conventions of previous Disney movies, especially with how they presented the "Prince Charming" trope as the antagonist, Gaston. He's an arrogant, selfish ladies-man who needs to save a damsel in distress (even if Belle doesn't want him to save her). In this episode of "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily and Sapphire examine the world of "Beauty and the Beast" to decide whether or not Gaston is technically ...

5.title: 41 Bad Conspiracies - Anniversary Special
5.plot: "Cartoon Conspiracy" just turned one year old and we want to thank you for supporting the show. For the last 12 months, we've received dozens of conspiracy theory suggestions on what our next episode should about, which had lead to some really fun episodes to work on. But every once in a while comes a ridiculous conspiracy theory that simply defies reason and must be addressed. So on this "Cartoon Conspiracy Anniversary Special", Emily and friends will rapid-fire debunk some of the silliest conspiracies ever.

6.title: The Little Mermaid/Hercules Theory - Ariel Related to Hercules?
6.plot: Disney animated films are known to make secret crossovers into previous films, even if they seem to take place centuries apart. Many have speculated that Ariel from "The Little Mermaid" and Hercules for, er, "Hercules" are actually somehow related to each other, being that they both children of supernatural beings. On this week's episode, Emily digs into the Disney family tree to find out whether this theory could be true.

7.title: The Batman: TAS Theory - Is Bruce Delusional?
7.plot: "Batman: The Animated Series" is easily one of the best adaptations of the famous comic book hero. With beautiful art design, awesome bad guys and amazing episode story-lines, it's no wonder that some people prefer it over the live-action films. But could the cartoon really just be a way of showing how delusional Bruce Wayne is to go out every night and fight super villains? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily steps into the caped crusader's boots to determine whether or not the show is really just the thoughts of a mentally ill Bruce Wayne in Arkham Asylum.

8.title: The Calvin and Hobbes Theory - Calvin's Fight Club?
8.plot: "Calvin and Hobbes" is one of the most cherished comic strips of all time, mostly due to it's polarizing yet relatable dynamic duo. Calvin represented the frustration of youth that all generations go through as a kid, only to be guided by his wiser (though imaginary) talking tiger, Hobbes. And it just so happens that one particular film shares similar traits with the comic, in that it follows an individual whose friend/voice of reason tells them what to do. This week, Emily will attempt to connect "Calvin and Hobbes" to the classic psychological cult film "Fight Club".

9.title: The Over the Garden Wall Theory - Stuck in Purgatory?
9.plot: There are few cartoon shows that can mix quirky storytelling with creepy visuals as well as "Over The Garden Wall", the cult-hit miniseries from Cartoon Network. The show follows two half-brothers who become lost in the creepy forest of "The Unknown" and encounter some really surreal and strange characters along their way, but could there be something else at work? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily will take the plunge and go over the garden wall to determine whether Wirt and Greg are actually just lost souls stuck in Limbo?

10.title: The Steven Universe Theory - Are Crystal Gems Evil?
10.plot: Ever since the hit Cartoon Network show, "Steven Universe" premiered to the world, many crazy fan theories have arisen. The show follows Steven and his guardians, the Crystal Gems, as they protect not only the sunny town of Beach City but the universe itself. However, what we think we know about their heroic intentions may not be actually not be correct. This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily asks the hard question; could the Crystal Gems actually be evil?

11.title: The Fairly Oddparents Theory - Happy Pills?
11.plot: Timmy Turner may have a miserable life but at least he has two fairy god parents to grant him wishes whenever he wants. They can take him on awesome adventures, give him superpowers or even just dive into a colossal chocolate milkshake. But what if his fairly odd parents aren't actually granting him wishes at all? This week, Emily wishes for some answers to see if Cosmo and Wanda are actually the bi-product of heavy doses of antidepressants Timmy has to take.

12.title: The American Dad Theory - Is Stan Dead?
12.plot: America needs a patriot, and there's no man more patriotic than Stan Smith from "American Dad". Stan's love for his country has always driven his desire for a world he deemed perfect, and technically he may have already gotten it. Stan's family were once devastated by the apocalypse, though by the end of the episode everything seemed to go back to normal. But what if every episode that took place afterwards were actually a form of Heaven that would allow Stan to technically live in his ideal world? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily will determine whether or not...

13.title: The Bob's Burgers Theory - Are They All Dead?
13.plot: The world of "Bob's Burgers" is a constant mix of comedy genius and disaster, which is what makes the show such a hilarious mess. Bob Belcher and his family-run burger restaurant have had some pretty crazy accidents, but have always been able to stick together through it all in the end. But what if one accident actually lead to most of the Belcher family dying except for Bob? This week, Emily examines the mind of Bob Belcher to see whether or not his aloof family are really just figments of his imagination?

14.title: Top Gravity Falls Conspiracies
14.plot: "Gravity Falls" is one of the most mysterious shows probably ever (cartoon or otherwise), with so many secrets hidden in each episode that you probably never noticed they were even there. That's why we've teamed up with the ever observant Lewtoons to count down the top conspiracies of "Gravity Falls". When you see all the hidden messages and Easter eggs that were hidden in plain sight, you'll just have to go back and watch the show over again. So get ready, because this week "Cartoon Conspiracy" is cracking the case of "Gravity Falls" wide open.

15.title: The Care Bears Theory - Voodoo Symbolism?
15.plot: The Care Bears have been a symbol for childlike innocence and warm-fuzzies since their debut in the '80s as both a cartoon show and toy brand. Which makes it all the more creepy to think that they may ALSO represent a certain black magic practice known as voodoo. This week on Cartoon Conspiracy, Emily is going to try her best Care Bear Stare to see if she can shed some light on this particularly dark theory.

16.title: The Inside Out Theory - Riley and Bonnie Are Related?
16.plot: Pixar has been known to make secret connections to their previous films in the newest films, which helps give the universe a more connected feeling. But when one character from "Toy Story 3" happens to share the same last name as the main character in Pixar's most recent film, "Inside Out", what could it mean? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily is going get in the head of two seemingly unrelated characters to see whether or not Bonnie from "Toy Story 3" is somehow related to Riley from "Inside Out".

17.title: The South Park-Kenny Theory - Stuck in Time?
17.plot: Over the course of "South Park"'s 18 seasons, we've seen a lot of stuff go down. Elderly citizens formed a militia, deadly dance contests took lives and even giant Cthulhu monsters have been known to show up. But the one thing that has always stayed the same is that one way or another; Kenny is going to die at some point in an episode. Could the reason for this occurrence be simply a gag, or are time loops to blame? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily is going to step into the world of the most death-prone kid that ever existed to try understanding this freak ...

18.title: The Beauty and the Beast Theory - Is Gaston Into Men?
18.plot: For Gaston (the antagonist of Disney's "Beauty and the Beast") the world just couldn't handle how manly he really was. He was born in a time when men were expected to be ridiculously strong and handsome, and no one had more of both than Gaston. But is it at all possible that the macho man was actually just compensating for a secret he'd been cleverly hiding for years? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily and Sapphire team up to decide whether or not it's at all possible that Gaston could be secretly gay.

19.title: The Steven Universe Lion Theory - Is Lion Steven's Mom?
19.plot: Throughout the series run of "Steven Universe" we've been introduced to some pretty crazy characters with amazing abilities, but few have been as mysterious as Steven's pink companion: Lion. But while the big cat's origins still remain a mystery, many have proposed the theory that Lion is actually Steven's late-mother. This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily will attempt to debunk whether or not Lion is actually Steven's mom: Rose Quartz.

20.title: The Roger Rabbit Theory - Actually About Racism?
20.plot: "Who Framed Roger Rabbit" is known for breaking all traditions of modern filmmaking by combining live-action footage with beautifully detailed animation. But while the mixing of the two mediums made for an extremely entertaining movie, the film's underlying themes represent a very different message. This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily takes on the world of "Who Framed Roger Rabbit" to see if the classic film is secretly about racial segregation.

21.title: The Peter Pan Theory - Is Peter Killing the Lost Boys?
21.plot: Peter Pan is well known for fighting pirates and having awesome adventures, but what do we really know about the child soldiers that follow him: The Lost Boys? What happens to them when they start growing up or and don't want to be kids anymore? Is there a darker side to living with an immortal, emotionally stunted flying boy? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily goes deep to uncover the secret life of the Lost Boys and the dark fate that possibly awaits them all.

22.title: The Rick and Morty Theory - The Original Morty?
22.plot: "Rick and Morty" follows the exploits of an alcoholic genius who drags his grandson across space and time for high concept sci-fi adventures. But is it possible that the Morty we know from the show isn't actually the original? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily will attempt to determine whether or not it's at all possible that there's an evil Morty who wants revenge on Rick.

23.title: The Magic School Bus Theory - Is Ms. Frizzle a Time Lord?
23.plot: In the world of "The Magic School Bus", Ms. Frizzle takes her class to all sorts of places that defy the laws of space and reality, much like a certain character from science-fiction; Dr. Who. Is the reason Ms. Frizzle has a seemingly infinite knowledge of everything because she happens to be the same race as Dr. Who? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily will use her powers of deduction to decide whether it's possible that Ms. Frizzle could secretly be a Time Lord.

24.title: The Aladdin: Genie Theory - Is Genie Really the Peddler?
24.plot: Out of all the the memorable characters from Disney's "Aladdin", the one everyone remembers the most is Genie. Voiced by the legendary Robin Williams, the character was made larger than life by it's voice actor's unforgettable performance. But there's one other character Mr. Williams played in the film than most people tend to forget; The Peddler from the intro. This week on Cartoon Conspiracy, Emily sifts through the sands to determine if it's at all possible that the Genie and the Peddler could actually be the same character.

25.title: The Berenstain Bears Theory - Alternate Realities?
25.plot: Who doesn't remember reading the classic children's books, "The Berenstain Bears" as a kid? And if that spelling made you question your own childhood memories, rest assured that you are not alone. More and more young adults are beginning to realize that the book series they remember referring to as "BerenSTEIN" is not actually accurate. But how could this happen?. This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily investigates this freak phenomena to determine whether not we're dealing with some alternate realities.

26.title: The Frozen Theory - How Did Elsa Get Her Ice Powers?
26.plot: There's certainly more than enough theories about Disney's "Frozen" to pacify hardcore fans, but even casual viewers want to know the answer to a burning question; how did Elsa get her ice powers? For a film with an impressive attention to detail, there wasn't any explanation as to why Elsa could control ice. That all changes this week on Cartoon Conspiracy, as Emily searches for the truth behind Elsa's ice powers.

27.title: The Clarence/Over the Garden Wall Theory - Same Town?
27.plot: At first glance, you wouldn't think that Cartoon Network shows "Clarence" and "Over The Garden Wall" would have anything to do with each other besides being great animated programs. But upon closer examination, there appears to a fair amount of concrete evidence that proposes the two not only appear in each other's shows, but ALSO take place in the same universe. This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily examines this strange cartoon anomaly between "Clarence" and "Over The Garden Wall" to determine whether the shows are truly connected.

28.title: The Invader Zim Theory - GIR Is the Genius?
28.plot: "Invader Zim" followed the hilarious plight of one ill-tempered alien trying to single-handedly take over all of Planet Earth alongside their robot helper, GIR. Unfortunately, despite GIR being a technologically advanced machine capable of independent thought, he only ever seemed concerned with partying and acting like a child. But what if GIR's taco-craving, idiotic personality was really just a facade to intentionally make Zim BELIEVE that he was dumb? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily analyzes everyone's favorite hyper robot to determine whether GIR is the ...

29.title: The Halloween Towns Theory - Nightmare Before Christmas
29.plot: "The Nightmare Before Christmas" and "Halloweentown" may only seem to be connected by being holiday Disney films, but they actually share more than a theme. Despite one being stop-motion and the other being live-action, the two both take place in a world called "Halloween Town", which other numerous similarities. This week on a very spooky "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily steps into another world to find out whether "Halloween Town" takes place in the two films.

30.title: The Popeye Theory - Android Created by the Government?
30.plot: Popeye the Sailor Man is one of the most recognizable cartoon characters of all time, and yet we know surprisingly little about the burly guy. Other than his obvious maritime background, many theories have surfaced over the years as to how he got his incredible strength and how his strange craving for spinach might be explained. This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily investigates whether Popeye the Sailor Man is simply extreme dieting, or if he isn't actually a human at all.

31.title: The Pokemon Theory - Where's the Original Pikachu?
31.plot: In the original Pokemon animated serious Ash and Pikachu are the best of friends. But is it possible that this Pikachu is not the original Pikachu?

32.title: The Aladdin Theory - Is Jafar the Good Guy?
32.plot: In the classic film, "Aladdin", Jafar is quite possibly one of the greatest arch villains in Disney history. At least that's how it seems since his nefarious attitude coincide with what we normally think of as a "bad guy". But is it at all possible that we've unfairly misjudged a man who simply has different outlooks on life? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily analyzes the great Jafar to figure out if it's possible that he's actually a good guy.

33.title: The Hey Arnold Theory - Is Helga the Protagonist?
33.plot: "Hey Arnold!" followed the adventures of Arnold and his friends growing up in the city, and the show was great about showing us the private lives of the show's enormous cast of characters. In fact, the character who's life we saw the most of was Arnold's secret admirer, Helga Pataki, and her constant struggle to hide her creepy obsession with Arnold. It made for some great episodes but looking back on it now, it would almost seem that Helga was the protagonist we were always rooting for rather than Arnold, who became more of a background character as the series ...

34.title: The Looney Tunes Theory - Is Road Runner CEO of ACME?
34.plot: We all grew up watching "Looney Tunes" but did anyone ever question why the Road Runner was so successful at eluding Wile E Coyote? Could it be that the Road Runner is CEO of ACME? This week on Cartoon Conspiracy, Emily goes undercover and will analyze one of the longest running feuds in history to determine whether we've been duped all along.

35.title: The Lion King Theory - It's All Shakespeare?
35.plot: If you've seen "The Lion King", you're probably familiar with a certain awkward family dynamic, specifically with Mufasa and his brother Scar. Scar wanted to be king of Pride Rock and went so far as to kill his brother to take over for the rest of the movie. But as it turns out, the story of royal betrayal has a lot in common with a certain Shakespeare play and it may have been intentional. This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily will determine whether "The Lion King" is secretly "Hamlet".

36.title: The Steven Universe Theory - Jasper Is a Fusion?
36.plot: "Steven Universe" is full of all sorts of crazy characters with mysterious origins, namely Jasper, the show's main antagonist. She's always been giving the Crystal Gems a hard time and doesn't hide her hate for fusions. But despite her disdain for them, she's fused with others in the past which makes her ideology a bit confusing. Could this be the belief of a truly unpredictable character or could there be a more mysterious reason? This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily will step into the mind of a villain to see if Jasper is secretly a fusion herself.

37.title: The Frosty the Snowman Theory - Frosty Is Evil?
37.plot: We all know the story and song about Frosty the Snowman, who magically came to live when a group of kids made him. They certainly had a fun-filled Christmas but doesn't it seem just a little too convenient? We hardly know the rules of this type of magic and what's really going on in that talking snowman's mind (if he even has one)? Without turning this harmless child's tale into something dark, we think it's still smart to revisit this holiday classic. This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily will attempt to tell if Frosty's try intentions are for good or for EVIL.

38.title: Is Sid Good? - The Toy Story Theory
38.plot: This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily will look into whether Sid from Toy Story is really such a bad kid.

39.title: Are Richie Rich & Casper the SAME Person?!
39.plot: This week on "Cartoon Conspiracy", Emily looks into whether "Richie Rich" died and became "Casper The Friendly Ghost".

40.title: Uncle Grandpa Is the Creator of Steven Universe?
40.plot: He's everybody's favorite Uncle, everybody's favorite Grandpa, and. - the creator of every cartoon we know and love?. Wait, so the crossover episode with Steven Universe is actually (sort of) canon?. Tim came up with a very unusual theory surrounding the mysterious life of Uncle Grandpa, and Emily is here to decide whether or not this conspiracy holds up.

41.title: Are Spongebob & His Friends Based on the 7 Deadly Sins?
41.plot: Spongebob Squarepants has been around for 17 years, and while Bikini Bottom may seem like a happy undersea oasis, does it really hold a deep, dark secret? Could it be that Spongebob, Patrick Star, Sandy Cheeks, and the rest of the Bikini Bottom crew are really based off of the Seven Deadly Sins? Find out the truth on today's Cartoon Conspiracy.

42.title: Is Princess Mononoke a Prequel to Totoro?
42.plot: Fans of Studio Ghibli would know that Hayao Miyazaki is a fan of repetition in his movies, but could this possibly mean that some of his movies are connected? Emily digs deep to decide if Princess Mononoke and My Neighbor Totoro not only take place in the same universe, but if Totoro is really a reincarnation of the Forest Spirit.

43.title: Are All Disney Princes A**Holes?
43.plot: We all grew up either wanting to be a Disney Prince or be with one. But have you ever stopped to think that maybe these "Happily Ever Afters" aren't actually very nice guys at all? Emily is here today to discuss the possibility that every Disney Prince is an absolutely awful person, and how these "Once Upon A Time" classics could have been an early set up for future failure in the love department for young boys and girls everywhere.

44.title: What's in the Krabby Patty Secret Formula?
44.plot: We've all wondered at some point or another, what *is* in the Krabby Patty Secret Formula that makes it so special? Is it salt? Barnacle Shavings? Turmeric? ...Love? Or, is there something more sinister behind the the secret formula? Emily is here today to give her theory as to what else might be in these delicious burgers to make them so irresistible to the residents of Bikini Bottom.

45.title: Best of Cartoon Conspiracy
45.plot: In honor of Emily's second to last episode of Cartoon Conspiracy, we here at Channel Frederator have put together a "Best of" clip show to look back on the past almost 100 episodes. With guest appearances and theories too good to believe, we're so proud of Emily and wish her all the best.

46.title: Is Magic Making Cosmo Dumber?
46.plot: When the Fairly Oddparents first appeared on Oh Yeah. Cartoons, Cosmo and Wanda seemed to be a pretty smart (albeit dimwitted) pair. But as the show's plot progressed and Cosmo's magical usage had increased, he seems to be getting dumber by the season. Could Timmy Turner's wishes be affecting Cosmo's intelligence? This week, Emily brings on a special surprise guest to get to the bottom of her final Cartoon Conspiracy.

47.title: Does Belle Have Stockholm Syndrome?
47.plot: While Beauty and the Beast is regarded as one of Disney's most romantic love stories, could there be something more to this story than meets the eye? What if Belle had actually developed Stockholm Syndrome during her time being help prisoner by The Beast? Guest host Sarah Snitch is here to lay out all the evidence and help audiences decide once and for all if this tale as old as time isn't as true as it could actually be.

48.title: 22 (Relatively) True Cartoon Conspiracies
48.plot: In this Cartoon Conspiracy compilation episode, we went back and found every single one of Emily's theories that were almost too good to be true and collected them in one mega-episode. From GIR's true intention on Invader Zim to Spongebob and his friends being based off the 7 deadly sins, find out which of the past 100 theories were (probably) true in the end.

49.title: Every Gravity Falls Conspiracy EVER
49.plot: Welcome to Cartoon Conspiracy. Dive into the mysteries and fan theories of all things animation with your host Emily as she takes a critical look at how the theories hold up.

50.title: Every Disney Conspiracy EVER
50.plot: For this week's Cartoon Conspiracy Compilation, we went back and put together every single Disney conspiracy theory we've ever discussed. From the possible family ties throughout the universe, to the heroes being mistaken for bad guys, we have every possible theory you could think of in the Disney continuity.

51.title: Is Zootopia About Racism?
51.plot: Disney's Zootopia has shattered box office records and become an instant animated classic, but there's more to meets the eye when it comes to everybody's new favorite film starring one determined rabbit and one wily fox. On the surface, Zootopia may seem like a fun film about overcoming the odds and following your dreams, but is this Disney film actually about modern instances of racism and prejudice in today's society? Sarah Snitch is here to break down the hidden meanings behind Disney's latest animated film.

52.title: Every Nickelodeon Cartoon Conspiracy
52.plot: In this week's Cartoon Conspiracy compilation, we've collected every single Nickelodeon conspiracy theory we could get our hands on. Relive all of your favorite Nicktoons moments as Emily discusses whether or not Danny Phantom and Timmy Turner are the same person, or if Sponegbob Squarepants and the his pals are based on the 7 Deadly Sins.

53.title: Every Guest Host on Cartoon Conspiracy EVER
53.plot: This week we're taking a look back at every guest host we've featured on Cartoon Conspiracy, and all of the crazy theories they've come up with. From Dexter's family being clones he made in his laboratory, to Timmy Turner and Danny Phantom being - THE SAME PERSON? Each of our guest hosts has a unique perspective on the world of cartoon conspiracies, and we've collected them all here for you today.

54.title: Are Reboots Good for Our Health?
54.plot: With the insane number modern adaptations and reboots of classic properties that have come about over the past decade, we have to stop and wonder: is Hollywood ruining our favorite nostalgic properties? And what's worse, could too many reboots actually be bad for our health? Today, Sapphire is here to discuss whether or not reboots are a good thing, and if they might actually be hurting us in the long run.

55.title: Riley's Hidden 6th Emotion?
55.plot: Disney's Inside Out was such a brilliant portrayal of every human emotion: Joy, Sadness, Fear, Anger, Disgust. But is there a hidden 6th emotion somewhere in the film that viewers didn't notice? Could this elusive feeling actually be Bing Bong himself, or is Riley missing a key emotion? This week on Cartoon Conspiracy, guest host Jacob Atkinson is here to break down what's really going on inside Riley's head and gets to the bottom of this potential conspiracy theory.

56.title: Powerpuff Girls Are All One Person?!
56.plot: The Powerpuff Girls are one of the most iconic crime fighting teams in cartoon history. And who didn't want to grow up to be Blossom, Bubbles or Buttercup? But is it possible that all of the Powerpuff Girls are actually just the personalities of one girl with Dissociative Identity Disorder? Today on Cartoon Conspiracy, our finalist in the search for a new guest host, Annie, discusses the Brenda theory and proves once and for all whether or not this conspiracy holds up.

57.title: Is the TMNT Multi-Verse Theory Canon?
57.plot: Since the 80s, the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles have gone through multiple transformations, iterations, and inter-dimensional vacations. Although each different version of the franchise exists within its own universe, is it possible that every version of these turtles with 'tude actually exist within the SAME multiverse?. Cartoon Conspiracy finalist R2ninjaturtle is here to break down this theory and determine once and for all if these turtle teams all exist within the same multi-verse.

58.title: Are Team Rocket from Pokémon Actually GOOD?
58.plot: Team Rocket's blasting off again. But what are the chances that they *wanted* to blast off, because they've secretly always been trying to HELP Ash and his friends?. Today on Cartoon Conspiracy, guest host Alyssa Levenberg gives her take on why Jesse and James could never seem to successfully kidnap Pikachu. What do you think? Could Team Rocket actually be - the good guys?.

59.title: Are All the Animals in Zootopia Vegetarian?
59.plot: In the world of Zootopia, predators and prey live in peace and harmony - so what do these animals have to eat? Clearly they can't hunt each other, so does that mean all of the animals in Zootopia are vegetarians? Today our guest host Greg is here to figure out whether or not there are other animals in Disney's latest animated film that are just there to be eaten, or if all of the sentient animals in the film are strictly herbivores.

60.title: The We Bare Bears Are NOT Brothers?!
60.plot: The bears from Cartoon Network's We Bare Bears are practically related. Whether it's biological or not, that's up for debate, but there's a lot of signs that point towards some seriously messed up childhoods - Where did the bears come from? How did they end up together?. Find out what we think on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

1.title: When Did Adventure Time's Great Mushroom War Happen?
1.plot: Adventure Time is full of mysteries and one of the largest, ongoing mysteries is exactly how the Land of Ooo came to be. We do know that the Great Mushroom War had a huge impact on shaping Ooo but what's not certain is when the Great Mushroom War happened.

2.title: Steven Universe's Onion Is Actually EVIL?!?!
2.plot: Steven Universe is full of characters that we love and love to hate. Ruby and Sapphire are the true OTP. Lapis is starting to open up to being on Earth. But what's up with Onion? Is he evil or just a troublesome child?

3.title: Recess Ideologies!? - Politics on the Playground
3.plot: Disney's Recess certainly captured the spirit of childhood and the freedom of the playground, but it also captured the all too real politics of the playground. Could it have done so by having each of the different groups of Recess represent real world ideologies?

4.title: Adventure Time Destiny Theory
4.plot: Most Adventure Time theories all seem to focus on the main plot, but there is another main aspect of the show: Destiny. So we at Channel Frederator ask, will Finn lose his arm again and is it his destiny for it to be permanent?

5.title: Is Steven Universe a Weapon Made by Rose Quartz?
5.plot: Rose is very clearly a master of military tactics. The leader of the Crystal Gem Rebellion against Homeworld and master tactician against the Homeworld armies, driving them away from Earth some 5 to 6 thousand years ago. However, if Rose is indeed the leader the characters describe her to be, there's one big question mark still at play. Where exactly does Steven fit into Rose's master plan? Is it possible he was created by her as a strategic move?

6.title: Codename: Kids Next Door Isn't REAL?!
6.plot: Codename: Kids Next Door was about a group of kids who were field agents in their organization's war against the tyranny of adults and they definitely get into some pretty wild stuff. It's almost to the point where the KND organization could never be real. Could it? What if Codename: Kids Next Door is actually just a very elaborate way of playing pretend and we're just seeing the show through the kids' eyes?

7.title: What Is Dipper's Real Name?!
7.plot: Gravity Falls became one of the most talked about animated shows because of the wealth of mysteries it provided. One of the biggest mysteries among the many in Gravity Falls was the outstanding question of what exactly Dipper's REAL name is. Even though his name was recently revealed in Journal 3, there were still plenty of fan speculation on what his name could have been. So in this episode, we have to say - Spoiler alert.

8.title: Is Danny Phantom Half DEAD?!?
8.plot: Danny Phantom. "Yo, Danny Fenton, he was just fourteen when his parents built a very strange machine!" Now, we all know the intro song and love the show, but is possible that Danny is actually half dead? Find out on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

9.title: Could Bill Cipher Return to Gravity Falls?!
9.plot: Gravity Falls is over, but the conspiracies don't stop. We were wondering, is it possible for Bill Cipher to return to Gravity Falls? Is he really gone? Is there more to his statue that is truly left behind? What the heck is an axolotl? We'll discuss it all, but if you haven't seen the show yet - SPOILER ALERT.

10.title: Does Mufasa from Lion King Control the Weather?!
10.plot: Disney's, The Lion King has a lion cub who learns some very important life lessons, such as the circle of life and of course, Hakuna Matata. Simba is taught by his father Mufasa even more valuable life lessons, even after he tragically dies. How does he do this though? Could it be that Mufasa controls the weather?.

11.title: Rick Knows He's in a Cartoon?! Rick and Morty Conspiracy
11.plot: Rick and Morty, has quickly become loved by all of us and we can't thank Dan Harmon and Justin Roiland enough for teaming up with Adult Swim to bring us such an amazing show. As we know, Rick breaks the fourth wall and has a lot of fun within the medium of television. In the show, there are universes upon universes of content. So could this mean that Rick know he's a fictional character? And if so, would this be why his world view is so nihilistic?

12.title: What Is Louise Belcher Hiding? Bob's Burgers Conspiracy
12.plot: Bob's Burgers could quite possibly be this generation's version of The Simpson's. Heck, we would totally watch 20 seasons of Bob's Burgers or maybe even a spin-off series with Tina Belcher. If Bob's Burgers continues for that long, one question will have to be answered at some point - What is under Louise's bunny ears and why does she always have to have them on?.

13.title: Animal Experimentation?! Family Guy Conspiracy
13.plot: Family Guy creator Seth MacFarlane has incorporated fully sentient animals into the communities of all his shows, including Family Guy, American Dad and The Cleveland Show. But what's the in-universe explanation for this? Were the sentient animals in Family Guy and other shows once human?

14.title: Is Saitama a God?! One Punch Man Conspiracy
14.plot: One Punch Man is one of the best new shows to come from Japan and we can't get enough. With the announcement of Season 2 of One Punch Man coming, we had to start thinking - what could really be going on with Saitama? Is it possible Saitama from One Punch Man is actually a God?.

15.title: Could the Over the Garden Wall Beast Be a Wendigo? WTF Is It?!
15.plot: Over the Garden Wall is an instant Halloween classic. As a mini-series produced by Patrick McHale, Over the Garden Wall is spooky and charming but still there's so much to the Uknown and the mysterious Beast. Could The Beast actually be a Wendigo of native folklore? Are there any other creepy monsters it could be?

16.title: Is San from Princess Mononoke Wearing a Dead Sibling's Fur?!
16.plot: Princess Mononoke is highly regarded as one of the best Hayao Miyazaki and Studio Ghibli films to date, but it's certainly has some mystery to it. There are many conspiracies around Princess Mononoke, including one that was confirmed by Hayao Miyazaki himself. So Cartoon Conspiracy is tackling Princess Mononoke, but this time with a theory about San. Is San wearing the fur of a deceased sibling?

17.title: Does Ash Have the Power of Immortality?
17.plot: We've had 20 wonderful years of Pokémon, but our main protagonist from the Pokémon anime Ash Ketchum is by no means 20 years old. Ash is clearly still that same young boy who first started his Pokémon journey nearly 20 year ago. So how does Ash stay forever young in the world of Pokémon? Find out on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

18.title: Is Chip from Beauty and the Beast an Orphan?
18.plot: Beauty and the Beast the animated film by Disney first came out in 1991. Now, in 2017, we're getting a full length live action movie starring Emma Watson. But one thing still doesn't quite add up from the original film - Chip, our favorite little teacup doesn't quite resemble Mrs. Potts when they turn back into their human forms. Does this mean Chip is actually adopted??

19.title: Momo Is an Airbender?!
19.plot: During Aang's journey in Avatar: The Last Airbender, it's NO coincidence that his trusty pal Momo is always there in times of need to help out when Aang needs him the most. Could there be more to Momo's role in Avatar: The Last Airbender?.

20.title: Is South Park's PC Principal Actually an AD?!
20.plot: South Park's 20th season has been one of the best seasons yet and with the addition of one the funniest new characters to grace the show, PC Principal, we can't wait for season 21. South Park has made jokes on just about everything, but with the latest story arc about ads it leaves us wondering if there's a connection between ads and PC Principal. Could PC Principal actually be an ad?

21.title: Is the Grinch a Mass MURDERER?! - How the Grinch Stole Christmas!
21.plot: The animated adaptation of Dr. Seuss' "How the Grinch Stole Christmas!" is a classic holiday movie to watch ever year for sure, but could the Grinch have actually done significantly more harm than once thought? Through the simple act of stealing a bunch of stuff, is it possible The Grinch put all of Whoville in danger? Is it possible the Grinch is a MASS MURDERER?.

22.title: Cartoon Conspiracy Hosts Answer YOUR Questions!
22.plot: Cartoon Conspiracy has been through a lot in 2016. Channel Frederator found new hosts for the show and the Cartoon Conspiracies got weirder than ever. We invited Jacob and Alyssa into the studio to meet in person, catch up and reflect on everything that happened on the show in 2016 and answer YOUR questions. So check out the Cartoon Conspiracy 2016 Special as we ring in the new year.

23.title: Are Adventure Time and Bravest Warriors in the SAME Universe?
23.plot: Adventure Time and Bravest Warriors share a very similar art style and it's no surprise since they were both created by the same creator, Pendleton Ward. However, this doesn't necessarily mean Adventure Time and Bravest Warriors exist at the same time, in the same "world" or even in the same universe. But could they...? We're tackling a big one here, so buckle up and get ready for one of the juiciest conspiracies yet.

24.title: Is Lincoln Loud ADOPTED??? The Loud House Conspiracy
24.plot: Nickelodeon's The Loud House is quite literally LOUD. The show is all about the Loud household, which has 11 kids running around, 10 girls and 1 boy, and wow. Things can get pretty crazy. Lincoln, being the only boy and having white hair does raise some suspicions though. Is it possible that Lincoln Loud is actually adopted?. Let's dive into this cartoon conspiracy and find out.

25.title: Regular Show Episodes Are Different Timelines?!
25.plot: Regular Show the animated series has officially ended. Let's take a moment for that to sink in. Cartoon Network's hit show just finished it's 8th and final season but we still dream about more adventures with Mordecai and Rigby. However, with every episode being so different - is it possible that Mordecai and Rigby's adventures have actually all been taking place in different timelines?

26.title: Who IS Pink Diamond?!
26.plot: Steven Universe introduces a new character to the series and everyone freaks out. Whether it's a new human or a new gem, fans go crazy and start speculating immediately. With the introduction of Pink Diamond in Steven Universe, this is still the case. So Cartoon Conspiracy is exploring - who exactly IS Pink Diamond?

27.title: Is the LEGO Movie a Sequel to ELF?!?
27.plot: The LEGO Movie surprised us all in 2014. We didn't expect a movie based on LEGO figures and play sets to be SO good and yet it was. One of the most surprising things was the appearance of Will Ferrell. Will Ferrell was in another film about making toys - could these movies perhaps be related? We've got just the Cartoon Conspiracy. Is the LEGO Movie a sequel to Elf?.

28.title: Gravity Falls and Rick & Morty Are Connected (Confirmed?!)
28.plot: Gravity Falls and Rick and Morty are two very different cartoons on two different networks, but is it possible that they are actually connected? Creators of each series, Alex Hirsch and Dan Harmon have a close relationship that definitely supports this theory, but there is so much more evidence throughout both series. So Cartoon Conspiracy is tackling this theory.

29.title: Shrek's Donkey Is Actually a Human Trapped in a Donkey's Body?!
29.plot: Shrek is known for a ton of talking animals in the magical world of Shrek, but why does Donkey seem to stand out more than others? Well, there's a very crazy conspiracy floating around that Donkey is actually a HUMAN trapped inside a donkey body. The crazy part is this conspiracy seems pretty believable the more we dive into it.

30.title: Is Jack Sabotaging His Plan to Get Back?!
30.plot: Samurai Jack is now back after over a decade of being off air, but Jack is still stuck in the future and has still not returned to the past. Why is Jack still stuck!? Is it possible that Jack is sabotaging himself in trying to get back to the past? Join us as we jump into this theory on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

31.title: Rick Is NOT a Genius. Rick's Secret Revealed?
31.plot: Rick and Morty is one of Adult Swim's most popular shows, but we are eagerly waiting for it to come back. However, one thing Rick might be hiding is how he got his smarts - Could it be that Rick is actually lying about how smart he is? What IS in his flask? Join us as we jump into this theory on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

32.title: Could Squidward Survive in ICE for 2000 Years?
32.plot: SpongeBob SquarePants, Patrick Star, Squidward Tentacles and the rest of Bikini Bottom have had a ton of adventures. One notable episode puts SpongeBob's neighbor Squidward 2000 years into the future after he accidentally freezes himself. Is this something that could actually happen? A frozen Squidward that survives and is just fine 2000 years later?. Join us as we jump into this theory on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

33.title: Pixar Theory Finally CONFIRMED? Finding Dory Updates the Pixar Theory
33.plot: The Pixar Theory has been around since Pixar's earliest films and has been building and building an even stronger case for being confirmed as more films have been released. Long time Channel Frederator fans will know that we covered the Pixar Theory on the channel a few years ago, but we thought it was time to revisit it. With the release of Good Dinosaur, Inside Out and Finding Dory, the Pixar Theory has been updated so we had to cover it here on Cartoon Conspiracy. So how does it hold up?.

34.title: Is Toffee the True King of Mewni?
34.plot: The show is called, Star vs. the Forces of Evil, but back when "Great Monster Massacre" happened, the alleged "monsters" attacked to resteal Mewni for themselves. And Queen Moon Butterfly is shown battling Toffee in the Grandma room. Was Toffee the previous king of Mewni? What if these monsters aren't evil at all? And what if Toffee is a descendant of the Butterfly family, making him the rightful heir to the Kingdom of Mewni? Could any of this be possible?.

35.title: Why Is Dr. Drakken's Skin Blue?
35.plot: Those of us who watch Kim Possible know the diabolical Dr. Drakken and his quest to dominate the world. But have you ever wondered why his skin looks different from everyone else? I mean, it's blue. Isn't that strange? Is having blue skin even possible? Channel Frederator is going to dig deep into the mystery of Dr. Drakken's questionable shade of skin with this Cartoon Conspiracy.

36.title: Is Patrick Star from SpongeBob a PSYCHOPATH?!
36.plot: SpongeBob SquarePants has been airing on Nickelodeon since 1999 and has had your favorite Bikini Bottom citizens a part of the main cast from the beginning. Squidward, Mr. Krabs, Sandy and our favorite starfish, Patrick Star. However, is it possible that Patrick has actually been a psychopath this whole time? Justin and Channel Frederator are tackling this subject on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

37.title: Is Greg from Steven Universe Actually Greg from OTGW?
37.plot: Over The Garden Wall left fans wanting more and theorizing just exactly happened to Greg and Wirt. Is it possible that Greg actually grew up and became a dad? Sure maybe, but what about Steven Universe's dad?. Sounds crazy, but this theory might actually be true.

38.title: Are Rick and Morty the SAME Person?!
38.plot: Rick and Morty surprised us all on April Fool's Day with the launch of Season 3 Episode 1, "The Rickshank Rickdemption". With this new episode so many crazy theories have sprung up regarding Rick and Morty Season 3. Sounds crazy, but this theory might actually be true.

39.title: Are Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy Actually FISH???
39.plot: SpongeBob SquarePants has some of the craziest characters around Bikini Bottom, but two characters look more human like than any other - Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy. But how are they the same size as the other fish around the town?. Could they ALSO be fish? Sounds crazy, but this theory might actually be true - Find out on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

40.title: Cars Destroy HUMANS in the Future?!
40.plot: Cars might be one of Pixar's biggest departures from the real world. There's no humans to be found. After watching the latest trailers for Pixar's upcoming sequel, Cars 3, there's STILL no humans!? So is it possible that Cars takes place in the future and have replaced humans? Find out on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

41.title: What Happened to Pua the Pig in Moana?!
41.plot: Moana's pet pig, Pua is only in the movie for a little while until Moana takes off on her own. What exactly happened to Pua the Pig in Disney's Moana? Is it possible that Pua the pig is actually an imaginary friend for Moana? Find out on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

42.title: Is Captain Underpants Actually Possible IRL?
42.plot: Captain Underpants: The First Epic Movie is hitting theaters this weekend and we are so excited to see it. Since Captain Underpants is based on being hypnotized, is it possible that Captain Underpants is actually possible?

43.title: Rick and Morty and the Secret of the Szechuan
43.plot: Rick and Morty surprised us all on April Fool's Day with the launch of Season 3 Episode 1, "The Rickshank Rickdemption". With this new episode so many crazy theories have sprung up regarding Rick and Morty Season 3, the meaning of the szechuan sauce and McDonald's involvement. Sounds crazy, but this theory might actually be true.

44.title: Is SpongeBob SquarePants Immortal?
44.plot: SpongeBob SquarePants lives in a pineapple under the sea. How long has he lived there? How long has he been ALIVE?. Is it possible that SpongeBob is actually immortal? Sounds crazy, but this theory might actually be true..

45.title: Are Woody and Buzz from Toy Story POSSESSED?!
45.plot: Woody, Buzz and the rest of the gang are just living toys, BUT is that all there is to it? Is there something deeper and darker happening in the Toy Story universe? Are these toys actually people back from - the DEAD?

46.title: Who Shattered Pink Diamond?!
46.plot: Steven Universe has had a ton of speculation around who actually shattered Pink Diamond. With the huge trial happening and all the most recent developments, the question still lingers - who did it!? Jacob has recently uncovered even more clues on cracking this case, so let's find out on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.

47.title: Why Ash ACTUALLY Got Pikachu in Pokémon?!
47.plot: Pokémon has had it's most popular character, Pikachu, at the center of the anime from the very start, but why was Pikachu actually given to Ash instead of a different Pokémon? Could there be a true reason why Professor Oak gave Ash a Pikachu instead of a different Pokémon? Find out on this episode on Cartoon Conspiracy.

48.title: What's Edd Hiding Under the HAT?!
48.plot: One of the oldest mysteries of any Cartoon Network show is what is under Edd's hat. Ed, Edd and Eddy never really answers this question though there are times when it is talked about. It's time we take a swing at cracking the age old question - What is under Edd's hat?

49.title: The Dead Bart Conspiracy EXPLAINED
49.plot: One of the oldest and most notorious Simpsons conspiracies is the mystery of "Dead Bart." The conspiracy states that an episode of the show is "lost" and was never to be seen by the public - except for a single fan who claims to have seen the episode, and shared details with the public. We've covered many Simpsons conspiracies on Channel Frederator, but this is a FIRST. So grab your pink donuts as we break down WTF is "Dead Bart"?

50.title: The Secret Behind Pickle Rick
50.plot: Rick and Morty surprised us all on April Fool's Day with the launch of Season 3 Episode 1, "The Rickshank Rickdemption". With this new episode so many crazy theories have sprung up regarding Rick and Morty Season 3 and even more speculation around the Comic Con footage and upcoming Season 3 premiere - we just HAD to cover the Pickle Rick cartoon conspiracy. So who or what the heck IS Pickle Rick?.

51.title: Evil Morty's Origin Theory
51.plot: Rick and Morty has shown us many, many version of Rick and Morty themselves, but one of them still brings up more questions than any other. That version, is of course, EVIL MORTY. Will we see more of Evil Morty in Season 3? Could Evil Morty's origin story be explained in an upcoming episode of Rick and Morty? So who the heck IS Evil Morty?. While we have covered this topic in a previous episode, there's a lot of new evidence that points towards new answers - Find out on this episode of Cartoon Conspiracy.
